Memo: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella is handing off some of his business responsibilities to Judson Althoff, who will become CEO of Microsoft's commercial business (Matt Day/Bloomberg)
Microsoft makes Xbox Cloud Gaming generally available, removing its beta tag after over five years, adds 1440p support, and raises bitrate quality to 27Mbps (Tom Warren/The Verge)
Microsoft raises the Xbox Game Pass Ultimate subscription price from $19.99 to $29.99 per month, rebrands Xbox Game Pass Core and Standard plans, and more (Tom Warren/The Verge)

Sources: Qualcomm adopts Arm's latest v9 architecture for its new generation of PC and phone chips, joining rivals like MediaTek and, analysts believe, Apple (Reuters)
Amazon unveils Amazon Grocery, a new private-label brand that offers 1,000+ grocery items largely priced below $5, available online and at Amazon Fresh stores (Robin Ajello/Bloomberg)
Amazon unveils updates to Luna, including adding AAA games like Hogwarts Legacy and new GameNight original party games, available to Prime subscribers (Jennifer Maas/Variety)
Google Home Speaker hands-on: the new $99 speaker is a similar size to the HomePod mini, comes in four colors, and Gemini is a vastly improved assistant (Jennifer Pattison Tuohy/The Verge)
Google unveils new Home products: $99 Google Home Speaker, set for spring 2026, third-gen $100 Nest Cam Indoor, second-gen $150 Nest Cam Outdoor, and more (Chris Welch/Bloomberg)
Meta says it will use users' AI chatbot conversations to help personalize ads and content, starting on December 16, but not in the UK, South Korea, or the EU (Meghan Bobrowsky/Wall Street Journal)
Google unveils Gemini for Home, replacing Assistant on smart speakers with new voice options and improved conversational skills, and a redesigned Home app (Abner Li/9to5Google)
Ray-Ban Meta Gen 2 review: an unobtrusive eye-level camera, improved battery, and lots of frames, but some may feel uncomfortable with a face-mounted camera (Jay Peters/The Verge)
Sources: the UK Home Office issued a new order to Apple in early September to create a backdoor into its cloud storage service, this time focused on UK users (Financial Times)
Oura unveils colorful ceramic Oura Ring 4 versions for $499+ in four finishes with enhanced durability and a thicker 3.51mm design, and a $99 charging case (Victoria Song/The Verge)
AWS and the NBA announce a multi-year partnership to launch new AI-powered features and data insights from games, including an NBA Inside the Game platform (Zaheer Kachwala/Reuters)
